From: Jan Kara <jack@suse.cz
Subject: blk-mq: Fixup kABI due to added parameter to bio_merge
Patch-mainline: Never, kABI fixup
References: bsc#1220631 CVE-2021-46984

Additional parameter to bio_merge function is kABI compatible because the hook
is only ever called from generic block layer code and in C arguments are
controlled by the caller. Just hide the additional parameter from kABI checker.

Signed-off-by: Jan Kara <jack@suse.cz>

---
 include/linux/elevator.h |    4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

--- a/include/linux/elevator.h
+++ b/include/linux/elevator.h
@@ -100,7 +100,11 @@ struct elevator_mq_ops {
 	void (*exit_hctx)(struct blk_mq_hw_ctx *, unsigned int);
 
 	bool (*allow_merge)(struct request_queue *, struct request *, struct bio *);
+#ifndef __GENKSYMS__
 	bool (*bio_merge)(struct blk_mq_hw_ctx *, struct bio *, unsigned int);
+#else
+	bool (*bio_merge)(struct blk_mq_hw_ctx *, struct bio *);
+#endif
 	int (*request_merge)(struct request_queue *q, struct request **, struct bio *);
 	void (*request_merged)(struct request_queue *, struct request *, enum elv_merge);
 	void (*requests_merged)(struct request_queue *, struct request *, struct request *);
